{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Take immediate action to save independent retail from dying",
        "additional_details": "We ask the government to:\r\n\r\nFund research on the impact of indie shop closures & online shopping on the UK economy\r\n\r\nSet up a retail crisis fund to provide emergency assistance to indie retailers \r\n\r\nIntroduce a law to protect indie retailers from greedy landlords, to include:\r\n- Tenant right to independent review prior to eviction (when landlords are in breach and/or retailers have history of lease compliance)\r\n- Tenant right to independent rent review when market and/or property conditions change.",
        "background": "The UK retail industry is in crisis and 100's of independent retailers are being forced to close their shops every week.\r\n\r\nIndependent shops provide employment, support their local communities and pay tax.\r\n\r\nIMMEDIATE and MEANINGFUL action must be taken to save independent retail.",
